    <div class="spiced-grid">
      <div class="sp-card">
        <div class="sp-letter">S</div>
        <div class="sp-title">Situation</div>
        <div class="sp-sub">Understand their reality</div>
        <div class="sp-desc">Map their current recruitment ecosystem. How is hiring structured? Who conducts interviews? What tools do they use? Are they scaling or optimizing?</div>
        <div class="sp-outcome">→ Clear understanding of their hiring setup and whether uman can create measurable value</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sp-card">
        <div class="sp-letter">P</div>
        <div class="sp-title">Pain</div>
        <div class="sp-sub">Expose inefficiencies</div>
        <div class="sp-desc">Make hiring challenges explicit and acknowledged. Unstructured interviews, bias, poor candidate experience, hiring decisions based on gut feeling.</div>
        <div class="sp-outcome">→ Clearly defined problem that leadership recognizes as important to solve</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sp-card">
        <div class="sp-letter">I</div>
        <div class="sp-title">Impact</div>
        <div class="sp-sub">Quantify the business case</div>
        <div class="sp-desc">Translate inefficiencies into measurable business impact. Cost of bad hires, lost productivity, manager time waste, compliance risk.</div>
        <div class="sp-outcome">→ Strong financial and strategic argument. Without quantified impact, there is no deal.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sp-card">
        <div class="sp-letter">C</div>
        <div class="sp-title">Critical Event</div>
        <div class="sp-sub">Why now?</div>
        <div class="sp-desc">Identify the trigger that forces action. Scaling this quarter? Leadership pressure? Preparing for funding? Recent bad hire? Deals close because of urgency.</div>
        <div class="sp-outcome">→ Clear timeline tied to a business-critical moment. No critical event = low closing probability.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sp-card">
        <div class="sp-letter">E</div>
        <div class="sp-title">Decision</div>
        <div class="sp-sub">Navigate the buying process</div>
        <div class="sp-desc">Drive alignment and close predictably. Map stakeholders (Head of Talent, HR Director, COO, CEO). Identify the economic decision-maker and internal champion.</div>
        <div class="sp-outcome">→ Structured buying journey with no surprises. Tailored demos, objection handling, mutual close plan.</div>
